    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4353cd37_bc2ede5f",
        "filename": "cmdrunner/command.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 230,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000487
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-06-17T14:06:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "When a timeout happens, a SIGTERM is first sent. Then the process may handle this and exit right away, normally. In this case, the task state should be:\n- state: TIMED_OUT\n- exit_code: \u003cactual exit code\u003e\n\nBut if the task doesn\u0027t exit in time before grace_period, then exit_code will be SIGKILL (15) or something like that. There\u0027s no difference in the task state if the process exited before the grace period or not. That could be something to fix later.",
      "parentUuid": "8f2dcd3e_a45f8473",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 230,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 230,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "ee78b7ef5d506d83e8e0f5e89409c463bfe08022",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
